node.text: Located on the Danish island of Bornholm is the Svaneke water tower. Designed by architect Jørn Utzon in 1952 (his first major commission - he would later design the Sydney Opera House) the 174 ft / 53 m Tower - whose design was inspired by Danish sea-markers (båke) is now a protected Danish Cultural Heritage Building. Photo: Phaidon #mcmdaily #jørnutzon #båke #betonbrut #denmark🇩🇰 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Shared from @annmarisauctions (lovely items - well worth following!) A selection of works from prolific Finnish designer Ilmari Tapiovaara. Trained as an architect Tapiovaara was greatly influenced by the designs of fellow countryman Alvar Aalto, whose company Artek produced many of Tapiovaara’s pieces. #mcmdaily #ilmaritapiovaara #artek #nordicmodernism #finland🇫🇮 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Some desert modernism with the Claire and Teddy Morse House. Located in Palm Springs, California the home was designed by architects William Krisel and Dan Palmer - with interior features designed by Hal Levitt - in 1961. Photos: Kelly Peak #mcmdaily #williamkrisel #danpalmer #hallevitt #alexanderhomes #fordmustang #morsehouse #desertmodernism #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Business with a view! The Owings House located in Big Sur, California and designed by architects Nathaniel Owings and Mark Mills in 1958. node.text: An interesting item with the ‘Solar Do-Nothing Machine’. Designed by Charles and Ray Eames in 1957 for the Alcoa Aluminum Company of America the children’s toy used solar power to produce motion in the multiple forms. Photo: Alcoa Aluminum Archives / @eamesoffice #mcmdaily #charlesandrayeames #eames #alcoaaluminum #vintagetoys #donothingmachine #usa🇺🇸 mcmdaily.com

node.text: Some béton brut located in Brasília, Brazil. Designed by architect João Filgueiras in 1969 the sprawling 21,000 sq ft / 1968 m2 home was recently renovated and restored by  Lutero Leme of Arquitécnika Studio. Photos: Edgar Cesar #mcmdaily #joaofilgueiraslima #betonbrut #brazil🇧🇷 mcmdaily.com
